page.title: 09HEDGEROW SURVEY (continued).
page.content: species in six hedges.They included:- fern,dandelion,cleavers,moss,hogweed, clover,meadow pea,knapweed,vetch,dock, meadow sweet,thistle,honeysuckle,hemp agrimony,rushes,nettle,St.John's wort, violet,bluebell,yarrow,chevil,wood sage,dogrose,fieldrose,birdsfoot trefoil,foxglove,nipplewort,pennywort, sow thistle,dead nettle,black bryony, selfheal,marjoram,convolvulus,campion, hemlock water dropwort,herb robert, herb bennet and hedge bedstraw.Trees found in hedges were beech,ash,oak,elm (but this was sucker growth),sycamore, hawthorn,holly,hazel,willow and black- thorn.One specimen of each of these was found:-lime,sweet chestnut and hornbeam.
